g.text: The story of streamgages tells the story of the evolving water needs of the nation.
The National Streamgaging program is funded by Congress
and over 1,400 state and local partner agencies.
It’s managed by the USGS, the U.S. Geological Survey, which has been operating gages for the last 130 years.
How much water can I release?
Can trout live in this reach?
That data is critical for water management.
Active gages collect water data and transmit it in real time.
Each dot on the map above is a streamgage.
